flowRoot.flowPara: A. A cause-effect relationship is identified within a large corpus of unstructured scientific text. This relationship is situated within a network of further causal relationships.
B. Semantic analysis automatically categorises the strength and number of causal statements, enabling a quick assessment of evidence weight and agreement.
C. The computer-driven analysis is refined by human users, who assess the statements and their contexts, accepting or rejecting evidence where appropriate.
